The following selections describe the specific characteristics which are unique
for the milestone chart.  Text Mode describes the available function keys when
in text mode and is split into two sections: the header and milestone/footnote.
The individual format options are explained in Format descriptions.  A brief
description of the milestone chart itself can be found in General description.
Also, the Graphics Mode, which is found only in the milestone chart, is
described when F4 is pressed.


To obtain help for any of the following subjects,  press the function key next
to the desired subject.

        F1  Text Mode
        F2  Format descriptions
        F3  General description
        F4  Graphics Mode
 
 
 
        F8  Return to Previous Menu
 
        F10 Exit from Help

Press F8 to return to the last menu screen or F10 to leave the help mode
